Andrew Gardner (@gardnerae), curatorial assistant in the Department of Architecture and Design, reflects on Greer Schütte-Lihotzky’s “maximally efficient” 1926 Frankfurt Kitchen design, the earliest work in the #MoMACollection by a female architect.

Explore our collection work by work as we release a new #UNIQLOArtSpeaks video each Friday, and experience the Frankfurt Kitchen in Gallery 513: Design for Modern Life.

@uniqlousa is MoMA’s proud partner of #ArtForAll.
